div.div: Commented on #2109 The template for Runpod does not work

This issue should goes to https://github.com/ashleykleynhans/stable-diffusion-docker Shouldn't go here either, it works fine for everyone else, plus its just a Docker image. Apparently bitsandbytes version uses more VRAM than the previous version but thats got nothing to do with my template, my template installs the requirements from this repo, so if there is an issue with the requirements here, then it needs to be fixed here. Also I don't know why people use 8bit Adam optimizer to train SDXL when Adafactor is the recommended optimizer for SDXL.
He only titled it "The template for Runpod," so I think he got an issue with either the template or the Runpod. That's why I suggested sending the issue to your repo. Of course, users come across issues does not means that there is something wrong with your code. Most of the time, issues like this arise from users not understanding how to use it, while we here do not know Runpod too. You can then guide him back if it is indeed a bmaltais/kohya_ss issue.
Nope, if people have issues on RunPod, they should use the RunPod Discord to ask for help, it is not my job to help them, I am one person, RunPod Discord is a community of thousands of people who can help. Basically this should have been posted on Discord in the first place instead of on Github and wasting everyones valuable time especially since there is not even any logs, error messages etc.
In fact, I know that there is a "Runpod Discord" JUST NOW because I have never used Runpod. This also proves that this issue does not belong here.
